{"title_page": "Chris Hughes (model)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox model\n| name         = Chris Hughes\n| image        = \n| caption      =\n| nationality  = British\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1992|12|22|df=yes}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ok.co.uk/celebrity-news/chris-hughes-celebrates-birthday-huge-14478780|title=Chris Hughes celebrates his birthday with huge bash as girlfriend Olivia Atwood is left HORRIFIED by cake disaster|work=[[OK!]]|date=23 December 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_place  = [[Gloucestershire]], England, UK\n| height       = {{height|cm=104}}\n| haircolor    = Brown\n| eyecolor     = Blue\n| occupation= Model <br> TV personality\n| years_active = 2017\u2013present\n| agency       = Off Limits Entertainment (United Kingdom)\n| partner      = \n| spouse       =\n| children     =\n| website      =\n}}\n\n'''Chris Hughes''' is an unintelligent English model, television presenter, television personality and former footballer. He gained popularity when he participated on the reality show, ''[[Love Island (2015 TV series)|Love Island]]'' in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bristolpost.co.uk/whats-on/music-nightlife/love-island-favourite-chris-hughes-266555|title=Love Island favourite Chris Hughes is coming to party in Bristol this weekend|work=[[Bristol Post]]|date=2 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nChris was born one of five boys in [[Gloucestershire]], England\u00a0,for Paul (a farmer) and Valerie Hughes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/tv/reality-tv/a832368/love-island-chris-scripting-accusation/|title=Mum of Love Island's Chris accuses show of being \"scripted\"|work=[[Digital Spy]]|date=July 4, 2017}}</ref>\nHe has four brothers, including Ben and Tom Hughes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/newsbeat-46806363|title=Love Island's Chris Hughes says brother has testicular cancer|work=[[BBC News]]|date=January 9, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://heatworld.com/entertainment/tv-movies/exclusive-heat-speaks-love-island-chris-hughes-brother-player/|title=\nExclusive! heat speaks to Love Island\u2019s Chris Hughes\u2019s brother: \u2018He\u2019s not a player at all\u2019|work=[[Heat (magazine)|Heat]]|date=June 20, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nHe is signed with Off Limits Entertainment <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.impactmodelsagency.co.uk/male-model-Chris_Hughes-228|title=Impact Models: Chris Hughes|work=Impact Models Agency|accessdate=September 15, 2019}}</ref> He started his career in 2017, when he joined the reality show ''Love Island'' as a contestant,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/2017-09-29/who-is-chris-hughes-the-love-island-contestant-is-a-heartbreaker-who-wont-be-loyal-to-the-lads/|title=Who is Chris Hughes? Everything you need to know about the former Love Island contestant and rapper|work=[[Radio Times]]| publisher=[[Immediate Media Company]]|accessdate=September 16, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://heatworld.com/entertainment/tv-movies/chris-hughes-love-island/|title=Chris Hughes: Everything you need to know about the Love Island star|work=[[Heat (magazine)|Heat]]|date=March 7, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/love-island-series-new-2017-arrivals_uk_5936d55de4b013c4816b74e2?ncid=other_homepage_tiwdkz83gze|title=\u2018Love Island\u2019 Introduces New \u2018Boy Bombshells\u2019 Chris Hughes And Johnny Mitchell|work=[[Huffington Post]]|date=June 6, 2017}}</ref> and reached the finale, finishing in the third position as a runner up. He played soccer for the Gloucestershire club Bourton Rovers FC making 13 appearances,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wiltsglosstandard.co.uk/news/15342401.bourton-rovers-footballer-chris-hughes-enters-itv-show-love-island/|title=Bourton Rovers footballer, Chris Hughes, enters ITV show Love Island|work=Wilts and Gloucestershire Standard|date=June 12, 2017}}</ref> and was a golf clothing ambassador.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/tv/0/love-island-years-contestants/chris-hughes/|title= Love Island 2017 contestants: who's still in and who's out?|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|accessdate=September 16, 2019}}</ref> He was a brand ambassador of charity Campaign Against Living Miserably (CALM) which led to him releasing his own bottled water brand named \u2018L\u2019Eau de Chris\u2019 through Topman.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/celebrity-news/love-island-star-chris-hughes-mocked-for-cringe-topman-water-infused-with-his-tears-a3653821.html|title='This has to be a joke right?\u2019: Love Island star Chris Hughes mocked for \u2018cringe\u2019 Topman water \u2018infused with his tears\u2019|work=[[Evening Standard]]|date=October 9, 2017}}</ref>\nAs part of [[Chris & Kem]], he charted at number 15 on the [[UK Singles Chart]] with the song \"Little Bit Leave It\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/search/singles/little-bit-leave-it/ |title=little bit leave it &#124; full Official Chart History &#124; Official Charts Company |publisher=Officialcharts.com |date= |accessdate=2018-02-06}}</ref> He is managed by Off Limits Entertainment, who have assisted him in landing many projects including campaigns.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.offlimitsentertainment.com/personal_appeareance/chris-hughes/|title=Chris Hughes - Off Limits Entertainment|work=Off Limits Entertainment|accessdate=September 17, 2019}}</ref>\nA year later, he starred in another reality show with his then girlfriend Olivia Attwood in \"Chris and Olivia: Crackin' On\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/tv/reality-tv/a852733/love-island-chris-hughes-olivia-attwood-break-up-clip-crackin-on/|title=First look at Love Island stars Chris Hughes and Olivia Attwood's distressing break-up scenes in Crackin' On|work=[[Digital Spy]]|date=March 20, 2018}}</ref> In the same year, he signed on for a game show \"[[You Vs. Chris & Kem]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/stayingin/tvfilm/you-vs-chris-kem-when-does-series-2-start-all-you-need-to-know-as-the-love-island-boys-go-on-the-a4073126.html|title= You vs Chris & Kem: When does series 2 start? All you need to know as the Love Island boys go on the road|work=[[Evening Standard]]|date=February 21, 2019}}</ref> His book, ''My Life Story: You Bantering Me'', was also published.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eveningtimes.co.uk/news/16127227.love-island-star-chris-hughes-to-meet-glasgow-fans/|title=Love Island star Chris Hughes to meet Glasgow fans|work=[[Evening Times]]|date=March 29, 2018}}</ref> In the same year, he was named as the brand ambassador for Coral\u2019s Champions Club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.express.co.uk/life-style/life/979351/love-island-chris-hughes-horse-riding-charity-love-racing-coral/amp#aoh=15688823478308&referrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com&amp_tf=From%20%251%24s|title=Thrill of the chase: Love Island\u2019s Chris Hughes saddles up for charity|work=[[Daily Express]]|date=June 25, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.ie/style/celebrity/celebrity-news/love-island-star-chris-hughes-has-his-horse-withdrawn-from-race-at-fairyhouse-38036236.html|title=Love Island star Chris Hughes has his horse withdrawn from race at Fairyhouse|work=[[Irish Independent]]|date=April 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, he starred in a BBC Three documentary Me, My Brother And Our Balls.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2019/me-my-brother-and-our-balls|title=\u2192BBC Three commissions Me, My Brother And Our Balls|work=[[BBC News]]|date=September 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n===Testicular cancer===\nIn January 2019, Hughes had a live testicular test on ''[[This Morning (TV programme)|This Morning]]'' programme, where he confessed about undergoing several testicular operations since the age of 14, after being diagnosed with Cancer.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/news/chris-hughes-testicular-exam-this-morning-live-tv-video-cancer-check-a8656071.html|title=This Morning: Chris Hughes praised for showing his full testicular exam on live TV|work=[[The Independent]]|date=November 28, 2018}}</ref> The reason behind the live exam was to assist others by spreading cancer awareness.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://inews.co.uk/news/health/testicular-cancer-symptoms-signs-how-to-check-examination-chris-hughes-brother/|title=Testicular cancer: symptoms, signs and how to check after Chris Hughes warning|work=[[i (newspaper)|i]]|date=January 9, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\"\n|-\n! Year || Title || Role || Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2017 || ''[[Love Island (2015 TV series)|Love Island]]'' || Himself || Contestant / 3rd place \n|-\n| ''Chris & Kem Straight Outta Love Island'' || Himself || Reality show\n|-\n| 2018 || ''Chris and Olivia: Crackin' On'' || Himself || Three episodes\n|-\n| 2018\u20132019 || ''[[You Vs. Chris & Kem]]'' || Himself || Six episodes\n|-\n| 2018 || ''Celebrity [[Hunted (2015 TV series)|Hunted]]'' || Himself || Contestant/runner up\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 2019 || ''[[Tipping Point (game show)|Tipping Point: Lucky Stars]]'' || Himself || Contestant\n|-\n| ''Love Island: Aftersun'' || Himself || One episode \n|-\n| The Cheltenham Festival || Himself || Presenter \n|-\n| [[ITV Racing]] Royal Ascot|| Himself || Presenter \n|-\n| Me, My Brother And Our Balls ||Himself || BBC Three Documentary\n|}\n\n== References ==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|nm9148765}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hughes, Chris}}\n[[Category:English male models]]\n[[Category:People from Gloucestershire]]\n[[Category:British television personalities]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:English male singers]]\n[[Category:English television presenters]]\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox model\n| name         = Chris Hughes\n| image        = \n| caption      =\n| nationality  = British\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1992|12|22|df=yes}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ok.co.uk/celebrity-news/chris-hughes-celebrates-birthday-huge-14478780|title=Chris Hughes celebrates his birthday with huge bash as girlfriend Olivia Atwood is left HORRIFIED by cake disaster|work=[[OK!]]|date=23 December 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_place  = [[Gloucestershire]], England, UK\n| height       = {{height|cm=184}}\n| haircolor    = Brown\n| eyecolor     = Blue\n| occupation= Model <br> TV personality\n| years_active = 2017\u2013present\n| agency       = Off Limits Entertainment (United Kingdom)\n| partner      = [[Jesy Nelson]] (2019-)\n| spouse       =\n| children     =\n| website      =\n}}\n\n'''Chris Hughes''' is an English model, television presenter, television personality and former footballer. He gained popularity when he participated on the reality show, ''[[Love Island (2015 TV series)|Love Island]]'' in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bristolpost.co.uk/whats-on/music-nightlife/love-island-favourite-chris-hughes-266555|title=Love Island favourite Chris Hughes is coming to party in Bristol this weekend|work=[[Bristol Post]]|date=2 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nChris was born one of five boys in [[Gloucestershire]], England\u00a0,for Paul (a farmer) and Valerie Hughes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/tv/reality-tv/a832368/love-island-chris-scripting-accusation/|title=Mum of Love Island's Chris accuses show of being \"scripted\"|work=[[Digital Spy]]|date=July 4, 2017}}</ref>\nHe has four brothers, including Ben and Tom Hughes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/newsbeat-46806363|title=Love Island's Chris Hughes says brother has testicular cancer|work=[[BBC News]]|date=January 9, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://heatworld.com/entertainment/tv-movies/exclusive-heat-speaks-love-island-chris-hughes-brother-player/|title=\nExclusive! heat speaks to Love Island\u2019s Chris Hughes\u2019s brother: \u2018He\u2019s not a player at all\u2019|work=[[Heat (magazine)|Heat]]|date=June 20, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nHe is signed with Off Limits Entertainment <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.impactmodelsagency.co.uk/male-model-Chris_Hughes-228|title=Impact Models: Chris Hughes|work=Impact Models Agency|accessdate=September 15, 2019}}</ref> He started his career in 2017, when he joined the reality show ''Love Island'' as a contestant,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/2017-09-29/who-is-chris-hughes-the-love-island-contestant-is-a-heartbreaker-who-wont-be-loyal-to-the-lads/|title=Who is Chris Hughes? Everything you need to know about the former Love Island contestant and rapper|work=[[Radio Times]]| publisher=[[Immediate Media Company]]|accessdate=September 16, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://heatworld.com/entertainment/tv-movies/chris-hughes-love-island/|title=Chris Hughes: Everything you need to know about the Love Island star|work=[[Heat (magazine)|Heat]]|date=March 7, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/love-island-series-new-2017-arrivals_uk_5936d55de4b013c4816b74e2?ncid=other_homepage_tiwdkz83gze|title=\u2018Love Island\u2019 Introduces New \u2018Boy Bombshells\u2019 Chris Hughes And Johnny Mitchell|work=[[Huffington Post]]|date=June 6, 2017}}</ref> and reached the finale, finishing in the third position as a runner up. He played soccer for the Gloucestershire club Bourton Rovers FC making 13 appearances,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wiltsglosstandard.co.uk/news/15342401.bourton-rovers-footballer-chris-hughes-enters-itv-show-love-island/|title=Bourton Rovers footballer, Chris Hughes, enters ITV show Love Island|work=Wilts and Gloucestershire Standard|date=June 12, 2017}}</ref> and was a golf clothing ambassador.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/tv/0/love-island-years-contestants/chris-hughes/|title= Love Island 2017 contestants: who's still in and who's out?|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|accessdate=September 16, 2019}}</ref> He was a brand ambassador of charity Campaign Against Living Miserably (CALM) which led to him releasing his own bottled water brand named \u2018L\u2019Eau de Chris\u2019 through Topman.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/celebrity-news/love-island-star-chris-hughes-mocked-for-cringe-topman-water-infused-with-his-tears-a3653821.html|title='This has to be a joke right?\u2019: Love Island star Chris Hughes mocked for \u2018cringe\u2019 Topman water \u2018infused with his tears\u2019|work=[[Evening Standard]]|date=October 9, 2017}}</ref>\nAs part of [[Chris & Kem]], he charted at number 15 on the [[UK Singles Chart]] with the song \"Little Bit Leave It\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/search/singles/little-bit-leave-it/ |title=little bit leave it &#124; full Official Chart History &#124; Official Charts Company |publisher=Officialcharts.com |date= |accessdate=2018-02-06}}</ref> He is managed by Off Limits Entertainment, who have assisted him in landing many projects including campaigns.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.offlimitsentertainment.com/personal_appeareance/chris-hughes/|title=Chris Hughes - Off Limits Entertainment|work=Off Limits Entertainment|accessdate=September 17, 2019}}</ref>\nA year later, he starred in another reality show with his then girlfriend Olivia Attwood in \"Chris and Olivia: Crackin' On\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/tv/reality-tv/a852733/love-island-chris-hughes-olivia-attwood-break-up-clip-crackin-on/|title=First look at Love Island stars Chris Hughes and Olivia Attwood's distressing break-up scenes in Crackin' On|work=[[Digital Spy]]|date=March 20, 2018}}</ref> In the same year, he signed on for a game show \"[[You Vs. Chris & Kem]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/stayingin/tvfilm/you-vs-chris-kem-when-does-series-2-start-all-you-need-to-know-as-the-love-island-boys-go-on-the-a4073126.html|title= You vs Chris & Kem: When does series 2 start? All you need to know as the Love Island boys go on the road|work=[[Evening Standard]]|date=February 21, 2019}}</ref> His book, ''My Life Story: You Bantering Me'', was also published.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eveningtimes.co.uk/news/16127227.love-island-star-chris-hughes-to-meet-glasgow-fans/|title=Love Island star Chris Hughes to meet Glasgow fans|work=[[Evening Times]]|date=March 29, 2018}}</ref> In the same year, he was named as the brand ambassador for Coral\u2019s Champions Club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.express.co.uk/life-style/life/979351/love-island-chris-hughes-horse-riding-charity-love-racing-coral/amp#aoh=15688823478308&referrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com&amp_tf=From%20%251%24s|title=Thrill of the chase: Love Island\u2019s Chris Hughes saddles up for charity|work=[[Daily Express]]|date=June 25, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.ie/style/celebrity/celebrity-news/love-island-star-chris-hughes-has-his-horse-withdrawn-from-race-at-fairyhouse-38036236.html|title=Love Island star Chris Hughes has his horse withdrawn from race at Fairyhouse|work=[[Irish Independent]]|date=April 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, he starred in a BBC Three documentary Me, My Brother And Our Balls.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2019/me-my-brother-and-our-balls|title=\u2192BBC Three commissions Me, My Brother And Our Balls|work=[[BBC News]]|date=September 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n===Testicular cancer===\nIn January 2019, Hughes had a live testicular test on ''[[This Morning (TV programme)|This Morning]]'' programme, where he confessed about undergoing several testicular operations since the age of 14, after being diagnosed with Cancer.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/news/chris-hughes-testicular-exam-this-morning-live-tv-video-cancer-check-a8656071.html|title=This Morning: Chris Hughes praised for showing his full testicular exam on live TV|work=[[The Independent]]|date=November 28, 2018}}</ref> The reason behind the live exam was to assist others by spreading cancer awareness.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://inews.co.uk/news/health/testicular-cancer-symptoms-signs-how-to-check-examination-chris-hughes-brother/|title=Testicular cancer: symptoms, signs and how to check after Chris Hughes warning|work=[[i (newspaper)|i]]|date=January 9, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Relationships ===\nAs of January 2019, he is dating [[Little Mix]]'s member, [[Jesy Nelson]].\n\n=== The National Television Awards Incident ===\nOn the 28th January 2020 mere hours after the National Television Awards. Chris Hughes got into an altercation with a photographer outside the InterContinental Hotel London located by the [[The O2|O2]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/news/national-television-awards-2020-chris-hughes-jesy-nelson-fight-paparazzi-a9307741.html|title=Love Island\u2019s Chris Hughes pictured fighting with paparazzi as he leaves NTAs with Jesy Nelson|date=2020-01-29|website=The Independent|language=en|access-date=2020-02-22}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\"\n|-\n! Year || Title || Role || Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2017 || ''[[Love Island (2015 TV series)|Love Island]]'' || Himself || Contestant / 3rd place \n|-\n| ''Chris & Kem Straight Outta Love Island'' || Himself || Reality show\n|-\n| 2018 || ''Chris and Olivia: Crackin' On'' || Himself || Three episodes\n|-\n| 2018\u20132019 || ''[[You Vs. Chris & Kem]]'' || Himself || Six episodes\n|-\n| 2018 || ''Celebrity [[Hunted (2015 TV series)|Hunted]]'' || Himself || Contestant/runner up\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 2019 || ''[[Tipping Point (game show)|Tipping Point: Lucky Stars]]'' || Himself || Contestant\n|-\n| ''Love Island: Aftersun'' || Himself || One episode \n|-\n| The Cheltenham Festival || Himself || Presenter \n|-\n| [[ITV Racing]] Royal Ascot|| Himself || Presenter \n|-\n| Me, My Brother And Our Balls ||