{"title_page": "Belladonna of Sadness", "text_new": "{{for|the album by Alexandra Savior|Belladonna of Sadness (album)}} {{Infobox film\n| name = Belladonna of Sadness\n| image = Belladonna_of_Sadness_Japanese_B1_film_poster.jpg\n| caption = Original release Japanese B1 film poster, as released by [[Nippon Columbia]]\n| film name = {{Film name| kanji = \u54c0\u3057\u307f\u306e\u30d9\u30e9\u30c9\u30f3\u30ca\n| romaji = Kanashimi no Belladonna}}\n| director = [[Eiichi Yamamoto]]\n| producer = Tadami Watanabe\n| writer = Yoshiyuki Fukuda<br />Eiichi Yamamoto\n| based on = {{based on|''{{cite web| title= La Sorci\u00e8re | url =https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/La_Sorci\u00e8re_(essai)| url-status=live}} [[Satanism and Witchcraft]] in the Middle Ages'', 1862, |[[Jules Michelet]]}}\n| starring = Aiko Nagayama<br />[[Tatsuya Nakadai]]\n| narrator = Chinatsu Nakayama<ref name=JMDb>{{cite web | url = http://www.jmdb.ne.jp/1973/cw001860.htm | title= \u54c0\u3057\u307f\u306e\u30d9\u30e9\u30c9\u30f3\u30ca / Sorrow of belladonna| quote= \u88fd\u4f5c\uff1d\u866b\u30d7\u30ed\uff1d\u65e5\u672c\u30d8\u30e9\u30eb\u30c9 1973.06.30 89\u5206 \u30ab\u30e9\u30fc\u3000\u30ef\u30a4\u30c9 / Production = Mushi = Nippon Herald, 1973.06.30 89 minutes color wide |publisher = Japan Movie Database| first=Y., ed. |last= Nomura | language = Japanese|accessdate=March 30, 2016| archivedate= March 19, 2016 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160319203516/http://jmdb.ne.jp/1973/cw001860.htm | url-status=live}}.</ref>\n| music = [[Masahiko Satoh]]\n| cinematography = Shigeru Yamazaki\n| editing = Masashi Furukawa\n| studio = [[Mushi Production]]<ref name=film>Opening credits of film</ref>\n| distributor = Nippon Herald Eiga <small>(Japan)</small>\n| released = {{Film date|1973|06|27|[[23rd Berlin International Film Festival]]|1973|06|30|Japan}}\n| runtime = 86 minutes<ref name=FJI />\n| country = Japan\n| language = Japanese\n| budget =\n| gross =\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''''Belladonna of Sadness'''''|\u54c0\u3057\u307f\u306e\u30d9\u30e9\u30c9\u30f3\u30ca|''Kanashimi no Belladonna''|also known as '''''La Sorciere''''', '''''Tragedy of Belladonna'''''{{refn|The film's title card bears, in addition to the Japanese title, the [[Latin alphabet]] title ''La Sorci\u00e8re'' (that of the source book in its original language). The [http://www.dailymotion.com/video/xdsg08_trailer-for-belladonna-of-sadness-1_shortfilms original trailer], [http://coilhouse.net/2010/08/the-tragedy-of-belladonna-2 posters] and video boxes use ''Belladonna'' as the film's Latin-character title. Mushi Production's Web site<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.mushi-pro.co.jp/2010/09/%E5%93%80%E3%81%97%E3%81%BF%E3%81%AE%E3%83%99%E3%83%A9%E3%83%89%E3%83%B3%E3%83%8A/ | title=''Tragedy of Belladonna''| publisher= Mushi Productions|accessdate= May 2, 2016| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20160305092837/http://www.mushi-pro.co.jp/2010/09/%E5%93%80%E3%81%97%E3%81%BF%E3%81%AE%E3%83%99%E3%83%A9%E3%83%89%E3%83%B3%E3%83%8A/ | archivedate= March 5, 2016| url-status =live}}</ref> and at least one online review<ref name=\"Sharp2006\">{{cite web|url=http://www.midnighteye.com/reviews/round-up_022.shtml|title=Round-Up #22: Anime special |accessdate=2008-08-26|last=Sharp|first=Jasper|date=July 3, 2006|publisher=MidnightEye.com | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120728095537/http://www.midnighteye.com/reviews/round-up_022.shtml | archivedate= July 28, 2012}}</ref> use ''Tragedy of Belladonna''.|group=n|name=tragedy}} or simply '''''Belladonna'''''}}<ref>http://www.tcm.com/tcmdb/title/489038/Belladonna-of-Sadness/</ref> is an adult 1973 [[feature film]] produced by the Japanese [[animation studio]] [[Mushi Production]] and distributor Nippon Herald Films. It follows the story of Jeanne, a peasant woman who is raped which leads to her being accused of witchcraft and is notable for its erotic, violent and psychedelic imagery.\n\n==Plot==\nJeanne and Jean are happy newlyweds in a rural village in [[France in the Middle Ages|Medieval France]]. Their idyll is promptly shattered when Jeanne, on her wedding night, is raped in a [[jus primae noctis|ritual deflowering]] by the local baron and his courtiers. She returns to Jean terrified and in pain, and he calms her, saying, \"Let us forget everything in the past\". That night, Jeanne begins to see visions of a phallic-headed spirit who promises her power. As a result, the couple's fortunes rise even as famine strikes the village and the baron raises taxes to fund his war effort. Jean is made tax collector, and the baron cuts off his hand as punishment when he cannot extract enough money from the village. The spirit visits once again (having grown in size) and rapes Jeanne in exchange for more riches. Although she submits her body, she attests that her soul belongs to God. Shortly after, Jeanne takes out a large loan from a usurer and sets herself up in the same trade, eventually becoming the true power in the village.\n\nThen the baron returns victorious from his war, and his wife, envious of the respect and admiration accorded Jeanne, calls her a witch, turning the town against her. Jeanne first tries to return home to Jean, but he refuses to open the door for her and she is assaulted. That evening, when soldiers come to arrest her, she flees into the nearby forest. In the wilderness, she finally makes a [[Deal with the Devil|pact]] with the spirit, who reveals himself to be the Devil. She is granted considerable magical powers, and returns to find the village has been infected with the [[Black death|Bubonic plague]]. Jeanne uses her powers to create a cure for the disease and the village flocks to her for aid. Having won their favor, Jeanne presides over [[orgy|orgiastic rites]] among the villagers. A page, who is in love with the baron's wife, begs Jeanne to help him seduce her. She gives him a potion that causes the baron's wife to accept his advances, but the baron catches his wife sleeping with the page and kills them both. \n\nPerturbed by Jeanne's power, the baron sends Jean to invite her to a meeting. The couple reconcile and Jeanne accepts the invitation. In exchange for sharing her cure for the plague, the baron offers to make Jeanne the second-highest noble in the land, but she refuses, saying she wishes to rule the entire world. Angered at her refusal, the baron orders Jeanne burnt at the stake. Jean is killed by the baron's soldiers when he tries to retaliate, which angers the villagers. As Jeanne is burned, the faces of the villagers transform into Jeanne's, fulfilling a priest's warning that if a witch is burnt while her pride is intact, her soul will survive to influence everyone around her. Centuries later, the influence of Jeanne's spirit initiates [[The French Revolution]].\n\n==Cast==\n* Aiko Nagayama as Jeanne\n* Katsutaka Ito as Jean\n* Tatsuya Tashiro as Witch\n* [[Tatsuya Nakadai]] as The Devil\n* Masaya Takahashi as Milord\n* Shigaku Shimegi as Milady\n* [[Masakane Yonekura]] as Catholic Priest\n* Chinatsu Nakayama as Narrator\n\n==Production and release==\n[[File:Belladonna of Sadness title card.png|thumb|350px|The film's title card, showing the original Japanese title \u54c0\u3057\u307f\u306e\u30d9\u30e9\u30c9\u30f3\u30ca, the original English-language title ''La Sorci\u00e8re'' and the U.S.-release title ''Belladonna of Sadness'']]\nDirected and co-written by [[Eiichi Yamamoto]] and inspired by [[Jules Michelet]]'s [[non-fiction]] book ''[[Satanism and Witchcraft]]'', it is the third and final film in the [[Animerama]] trilogy and the only one to be neither written nor directed by [[Osamu Tezuka]] (he left Mushi Production during the film's early stages to concentrate on his [[manga]]<ref name=\"Sharp2006\"/> and his conceptual-stage contribution is uncredited). ''Belladonna'' is also of a more serious tone than the more comedic first two Animerama films. Its visuals consist mostly of still paintings panned across<ref name=\"Sharp2006\" /> and are influenced by western art, such as that of [[Gustav Klimt]],<ref name=\"Sharp2006\" /> and [[Tarot]] illustrations (see also the work of [[Aubrey Beardsley]] and [[Harry Clarke]]). Production of the film lasted from 1967 to 1973. The film was a commercial failure and contributed to Mushi Pro becoming bankrupt by the end of the year.<ref name=\"Sharp2006\" /> The film was entered into the [[23rd Berlin International Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.berlinale.de/en/archiv/jahresarchive/1973/01_jahresblatt_1973/01_Jahresblatt_1973.html | title = 23rd Berlin International Film Festival June 22 - July 3, 1973|publisher=[[Berlin International Film Festival|66th Internationale Filmfestspiele Berlin]] | place = DE | language = English| archivedate= March 3, 2016| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20160303202742/http://www.berlinale.de/en/archiv/jahresarchive/1973/01_jahresblatt_1973/01_Jahresblatt_1973.html| url-status=live}}.</ref> \n\nThe film was released wide in Europe and Japan, received a limited screening in the U.S. in 2009<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141119121949/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2009-01-09/paprika-belladonna-of-sadness-mind-game-in-la-this-month|archivedate=November 19, 2014|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2009-01-09/paprika-belladonna-of-sadness-mind-game-in-la-this-month|title=Paprika, Belladonna of Sadness, Mind Game in LA This Month (Updated)|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 9, 2009|accessdate=October 26, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> and has undergone a 4K digital restoration for theatrical release in May 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cineliciouspics.com/belladonna-of-sadness/|title=''Belladonna of Sadness''|publisher= Cinelicious Pics|language=en-US|access-date=March 15, 2016|archivedate=March 21, 2016| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20160321211028/http://www.cineliciouspics.com/belladonna-of-sadness/ | url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.indiewire.com/article/belladonna-of-sadness-movie-poster-restoration-20160321|title=Poster for Long-Lost 'Belladonna of Sadness' is Cleverly Censored for an American Audience| first= Jake |last=Spencer | publisher=[[Indiewire.com]] | date=March 21, 2016 |accessdate= March 30, 2016|archivedate=March 23, 2016| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20160323074256/http://www.indiewire.com/article/belladonna-of-sadness-movie-poster-restoration-20160321 | url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe restoration was screened on July 10, 2015 in a \"sneak preview\" at [[Japan Cuts]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.japansociety.org/event/belladonna-of-sadness-4k-restoration |title=''Belladonna of Sadness'' (4K restoration)|publisher=[[Japan Society (Manhattan)|Japan Society]]|location = New York City |accessdate=June 9, 2016|archivedate= November 6, 2015| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151106180836/http://www.japansociety.org/event/belladonna-of-sadness-4k-restoration | url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/07/05/movies/japan-cuts-film-festival-at-japan-society-emphasizes-the-eccentric.html |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |title=Japan Cuts Film Festival at Japan Society Emphasizes the Eccentric |first=Mike |last=Hale |date=July 3, 2016 |accessdate=June 9, 2016 |archivedate=June 13, 2016 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6iDplprBi?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2015/07/05/movies/japan-cuts-film-festival-at-japan-society-emphasizes-the-eccentric.html?_r=1 |url-status=live }}</ref> and then played on September 24, 2015 at [[Fantastic Fest]] in Austin<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fantasticfest.com/films/belladonna-of-sadness |title=''Belladonna of Sadness'' |publisher=[[Fantastic Fest]] |accessdate=June 9, 2016| archivedate=March 22, 2016 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160322005310/http://fantasticfest.com/films/belladonna-of-sadness | url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Exclusive: Inside Japan\u2019s Lost Erotic \u201970s Anime \u2018Belladonna of Sadness\u2019  |url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2015/09/28/exclusive-inside-japan-s-lost-erotic-70s-anime-belladonna-of-sadness.html |author=Jen Yamato |date=2015-09-27 |accessdate=2016-06-09 |publisher=TheDailyBeast.com|archivedate= January 25, 2016| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20160125070156/http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2015/09/28/exclusive-inside-japan-s-lost-erotic-70s-anime-belladonna-of-sadness.html | url-status =live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2015/09/23/fantastic-fest-2015-16-must-see-movies |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |title=16 must-see movies at Fantastic Fest 2015 |first=Clark|last= Collis |accessdate=June 9, 2016| archivedate=November 1, 2015 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151101091837/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/09/23/fantastic-fest-2015-16-must-see-movies | url-status=live}}</ref> before a theatrical run beginning May 6, 2016 in New York City and San Francisco.<ref>{{cite web|title=Review: \u2018Belladonna of Sadness,\u2019 a Bewitching Masterpiece |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/05/06/movies/belladonna-of-sadness-review-japanese-animation.html |first=Glenn |last=Kenny |date=May 5, 2016 |accessdate=June 9, 2016 |archivedate=June 13, 2016 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6iDqckmEw?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/05/06/movies/belladonna-of-sadness-review-japanese-animation.html?_r=0 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/05/06/elijah-wood-belladonna-sadness |work=Entertainment Weekly |title=See why Elijah Wood's mind was blown by animated film Belladonna of Sadness\u2014Exclusive clip |first=Clark|last= Collis |date=May 6, 2016 |accessdate=June 9, 2016| archivedate= May 16, 2016| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160516085850/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/05/06/elijah-wood-belladonna-sadness| url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2016/02/watch-long-lost-belladonna-of-sadness-gets-a-psychedelic-nsfw-trailer-67920/ |publisher=Indiewire.com |title=Watch: Long-Lost \u2018Belladonna of Sadness\u2019 Gets a Psychedelic NSFW Trailer |accessdate=June 9, 2016|archivedate=June 13, 2016 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613003520/http://www.indiewire.com/2016/02/watch-long-lost-belladonna-of-sadness-gets-a-psychedelic-nsfw-trailer-67920/ | url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBecause of the film's obscurity, various sources list its running time as anywhere from 86 to 93 minutes. [[Cinelicious Pics]] clarified in May 2016 that its 86-minute restoration represented the correct running time, saying that this length had been {{quote|cut down by approximately eight minutes for an unsuccessful re-release in Japan in 1979 (with the addition of the brief ending shot of Eugene Delacroix's painting ''[[Liberty Leading the People]]'', which wasn't in the original version\u2014Cinelicious left it in this restored version). Cinelicious restored the censored footage from the sole surviving 35mm release print of the full-length version at the Cinematek in Belgium, which very graciously agreed to do a 4K scan of the missing sections from their print.<ref name=FJI>Cinelicious Pics spokesperson quoted in {{cite news| url=http://www.filmjournal.com/reviews/film-review-belladonna-sadness|title=Film Review: Belladonna of Sadness||first= Frank|last= Lovece |date=May 5, 2016|accessdate= June 12, 2016| work=[[Film Journal International]] | archivedate=June 13, 2016| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613001212/http://www.filmjournal.com/reviews/film-review-belladonna-sadness | url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of animated feature-length films]]\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{Reflist|group=n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0071203}}\n* {{Amg movie|155590}}\n* {{ann|film|1723}}\n* {{YouTube|2WkcLMapo_Y|Cinelicious trailer}}\n* {{YouTube|uIs1CT__ZBM|Original Japanese trailer}}\n\n{{Osamu Tezuka}}\n\n[[Category:1973 anime films]]\n[[Category:Adult animated films]]\n[[Category:Animated feature films]]\n[[Category:Films about sexuality]]\n[[Category:Films based on non-fiction books]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Eiichi Yamamoto]]\n[[Category:Films about Joan of Arc]]\n[[Category:Osamu Tezuka anime]]\n[[Category:Mushi Production]]\n[[Category:Japanese films]]\n[[Category:Films about witchcraft]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the album by Alexandra Savior|Belladonna of Sadness (album)}} {{Infobox film\n| name = Belladonna of Sadness\n| image = Belladonna_of_Sadness_Japanese_B1_film_poster.jpg\n| caption = Original release Japanese B1 film poster, as released by [[Nippon Columbia]]\n| film name = {{Film name| kanji = \u54c0\u3057\u307f\u306e\u30d9\u30e9\u30c9\u30f3\u30ca\n| romaji = Kanashimi no Belladonna}}\n| director = [[Eiichi Yamamoto]]\n| producer = Tadami Watanabe\n| writer = Yoshiyuki Fukuda<br />Eiichi Yamamoto\n| based on = {{based on|''La Sorci\u00e8re,[[Satanism and Witchcraft]]in the Middle Ages''|[[Jules Michelet]]}}\n| starring = Aiko Nagayama<br />[[Tatsuya Nakadai]]\n| narrator = Chinatsu Nakayama<ref name=JMDb>{{cite web | url = http://www.jmdb.ne.jp/1973/cw001860.htm | title= \u54c0\u3057\u307f\u306e\u30d9\u30e9\u30c9\u30f3\u30ca / Sorrow of belladonna| quote= \u88fd\u4f5c\uff1d\u866b\u30d7\u30ed\uff1d\u65e5\u672c\u30d8\u30e9\u30eb\u30c9 1973.06.30 89\u5206 \u30ab\u30e9\u30fc\u3000\u30ef\u30a4\u30c9 / Production = Mushi = Nippon Herald, 1973.06.30 89 minutes color wide |publisher = Japan Movie Database| first=Y., ed. |last= Nomura | language = Japanese|accessdate=March 30, 2016| archivedate= March 19, 2016 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160319203516/http://jmdb.ne.jp/1973/cw001860.htm | url-status=live}}.</ref>\n| music = [[Masahiko Satoh]]\n| cinematography = Shigeru Yamazaki\n| editing = Masashi Furukawa\n| studio = [[Mushi Production]]<ref name=film>Opening credits of film</ref>\n| distributor = Nippon Herald Eiga <small>(Japan)</small>\n| released = {{Film date|1973|06|27|[[23rd Berlin International Film Festival]]|1973|06|30|Japan}}\n| runtime = 86 minutes<ref name=FJI />\n| country = Japan\n| language = Japanese\n| budget =\n| gross =\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''''Belladonna of Sadness'''''|\u54c0\u3057\u307f\u306e\u30d9\u30e9\u30c9\u30f3\u30ca|''Kanashimi no Belladonna''|also known as '''''La Sorciere''''', '''''Tragedy of Belladonna'''''{{refn|The film's title card bears, in addition to the Japanese title, the [[Latin alphabet]] title ''La Sorci\u00e8re'' (that of the source book in its original language). The [http://www.dailymotion.com/video/xdsg08_trailer-for-belladonna-of-sadness-1_shortfilms original trailer], [http://coilhouse.net/2010/08/the-tragedy-of-belladonna-2 posters] and video boxes use ''Belladonna'' as the film's Latin-character title. Mushi Production's Web site<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.mushi-pro.co.jp/2010/09/%E5%93%80%E3%81%97%E3%81%BF%E3%81%AE%E3%83%99%E3%83%A9%E3%83%89%E3%83%B3%E3%83%8A/ | title=''Tragedy of Belladonna''| publisher= Mushi Productions|accessdate= May 2, 2016| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20160305092837/http://www.mushi-pro.co.jp/2010/09/%E5%93%80%E3%81%97%E3%81%BF%E3%81%AE%E3%83%99%E3%83%A9%E3%83%89%E3%83%B3%E3%83%8A/ | archivedate= March 5, 2016| url-status =live}}</ref> and at least one online review<ref name=\"Sharp2006\">{{cite web|url=http://www.midnighteye.com/reviews/round-up_022.shtml|title=Round-Up #22: Anime special |accessdate=2008-08-26|last=Sharp|first=Jasper|date=July 3, 2006|publisher=MidnightEye.com | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120728095537/http://www.midnighteye.com/reviews/round-up_022.shtml | archivedate= July 28, 2012}}</ref> use ''Tragedy of Belladonna''.|group=n|name=tragedy}} or simply '''''Belladonna'''''}}<ref>http://www.tcm.com/tcmdb/title/489038/Belladonna-of-Sadness/</ref> is an adult 1973 [[feature film]] produced by the Japanese [[animation studio]] [[Mushi Production]] and distributor Nippon Herald Films. It follows the story of Jeanne, a peasant woman who is raped which leads to her being accused of witchcraft and is notable for its erotic, violent and psychedelic imagery.\n\n==Plot==\nJeanne and Jean are happy newlyweds in a rural village in [[France in the Middle Ages|Medieval France]]. Their idyll is promptly shattered when Jeanne, on her wedding night, is raped in a [[jus primae noctis|ritual deflowering]] by the local baron and his courtiers. She returns to Jean terrified and in pain, and he calms her, saying, \"Let us forget everything in the past\". That night, Jeanne begins to see visions of a phallic-headed spirit who promises her power. As a result, the couple's fortunes rise even as famine strikes the village and the baron raises taxes to fund his war effort. Jean is made tax collector, and the baron cuts off his hand as punishment when he cannot extract enough money from the village. The spirit visits once again (having grown in size) and rapes Jeanne in exchange for more riches. Although she submits her body, she attests that her soul belongs to God. Shortly after, Jeanne takes out a large loan from a usurer and sets herself up in the same trade, eventually becoming the true power in the village.\n\nThen the baron returns victorious from his war, and his wife, envious of the respect and admiration accorded Jeanne, calls her a witch, turning the town against her. Jeanne first tries to return home to Jean, but he refuses to open the door for her and she is assaulted. That evening, when soldiers come to arrest her, she flees into the nearby forest. In the wilderness, she finally makes a [[Deal with the Devil|pact]] with the spirit, who reveals himself to be the Devil. She is granted considerable magical powers, and returns to find the village has been infected with the [[Black death|Bubonic plague]]. Jeanne uses her powers to create a cure for the disease and the village flocks to her for aid. Having won their favor, Jeanne presides over [[orgy|orgiastic rites]] among the villagers. A page, who is in love with the baron's wife, begs Jeanne to help him seduce her. She gives him a potion that causes the baron's wife to accept his advances, but the baron catches his wife sleeping with the page and kills them both. \n\nPerturbed by Jeanne's power, the baron sends Jean to invite her to a meeting. The couple reconcile and Jeanne accepts the invitation. In exchange for sharing her cure for the plague, the baron offers to make Jeanne the second-highest noble in the land, but she refuses, saying she wishes to rule the entire world. Angered at her refusal, the baron orders Jeanne burnt at the stake. Jean is killed by the baron's soldiers when he tries to retaliate, which angers the villagers. As Jeanne is burned, the faces of the villagers transform into Jeanne's, fulfilling a priest's warning that if a witch is burnt while her pride is intact, her soul will survive to influence everyone around her. Centuries later, the influence of Jeanne's spirit initiates [[The French Revolution]].\n\n==Cast==\n* Aiko Nagayama as Jeanne\n* Katsutaka Ito as Jean\n* Tatsuya Tashiro as Witch\n* [[Tatsuya Nakadai]] as The Devil\n* Masaya Takahashi as Milord\n* Shigaku Shimegi as Milady\n* [[Masakane Yonekura]] as Catholic Priest\n* Chinatsu Nakayama as Narrator\n\n==Production and release==\n[[File:Belladonna of Sadness title card.png|thumb|350px|The film's title card, showing the original Japanese title \u54c0\u3057\u307f\u306e\u30d9\u30e9\u30c9\u30f3\u30ca, the original English-language title ''La Sorci\u00e8re'' and the U.S.-release title ''Belladonna of Sadness'']]\nDirected and co-written by [[Eiichi Yamamoto]] and inspired by [[Jules Michelet]]'s [[non-fiction]] book ''[[Satanism and Witchcraft]]'', it is the third and final film in the [[Animerama]] trilogy and the only one to be neither written nor directed by [[Osamu Tezuka]] (he left Mushi Production during the film's early stages to concentrate on his [[manga]]<ref name=\"Sharp2006\"/> and his conceptual-stage contribution is uncredited). ''Belladonna'' is also of a more serious tone than the more comedic first two Animerama films. Its visuals consist mostly of still paintings panned across<ref name=\"Sharp2006\" /> and are influenced by western art, such as that of [[Gustav Klimt]],<ref name=\"Sharp2006\" /> and [[Tarot]] illustrations (see also the work of [[Aubrey Beardsley]] and [[Harry Clarke]]). Production of the film lasted from 1967 to 1973. The film was a commercial failure and contributed to Mushi Pro becoming bankrupt by the end of the year.<ref name=\"Sharp2006\" /> The film was entered into the [[23rd Berlin International Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.berlinale.de/en/archiv/jahresarchive/1973/01_jahresblatt_1973/01_Jahresblatt_1973.html | title = 23rd Berlin International Film Festival June 22 - July 3, 1973|publisher=[[Berlin International Film Festival|66th Internationale Filmfestspiele Berlin]] | place = DE | language = English| archivedate= March 3, 2016| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20160303202742/http://www.berlinale.de/en/archiv/jahresarchive/1973/01_jahresblatt_1973/01_Jahresblatt_1973.html| url-status=live}}.</ref> \n\nThe film was released wide in Europe and Japan, received a limited screening in the U.S. in 2009<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141119121949/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2009-01-09/paprika-belladonna-of-sadness-mind-game-in-la-this-month|archivedate=November 19, 2014|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2009-01-09/paprika-belladonna-of-sadness-mind-game-in-la-this-month|title=Paprika, Belladonna of Sadness, Mind Game in LA This Month (Updated)|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 9, 2009|accessdate=October 26, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> and has undergone a 4K digital restoration for theatrical release in May 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cineliciouspics.com/belladonna-of-sadness/|title=''Belladonna of Sadness''|publisher= Cinelicious Pics|language=en-US|access-date=March 15, 2016|archivedate=March 21, 2016| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20160321211028/http://www.cineliciouspics.com/belladonna-of-sadness/ | url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.indiewire.com/article/belladonna-of-sadness-movie-poster-restoration-20160321|title=Poster for Long-Lost 'Belladonna of Sadness' is Cleverly Censored for an American Audience| first= Jake |last=Spencer | publisher=[[Indiewire.com]] | date=March 21, 2016 |accessdate= March 30, 2016|archivedate=March 23, 2016| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20160323074256/http://www.indiewire.com/article/belladonna-of-sadness-movie-poster-restoration-20160321 | url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe restoration was screened on July 10, 2015 in a \"sneak preview\" at [[Japan Cuts]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.japansociety.org/event/belladonna-of-sadness-4k-restoration |title=''Belladonna of Sadness'' (4K restoration)|publisher=[[Japan Society (Manhattan)|Japan Society]]|location = New York City |accessdate=June 9, 2016|archivedate= November 6, 2015| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151106180836/http://www.japansociety.org/event/belladonna-of-sadness-4k-restoration | url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/07/05/movies/japan-cuts-film-festival-at-japan-society-emphasizes-the-eccentric.html |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |title=Japan Cuts Film Festival at Japan Society Emphasizes the Eccentric |first=Mike |last=Hale |date=July 3, 2016 |accessdate=June 9, 2016 |archivedate=June 13, 2016 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6iDplprBi?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2015/07/05/movies/japan-cuts-film-festival-at-japan-society-emphasizes-the-eccentric.html?_r=1 |url-status=live }}</ref> and then played on September 24, 2015 at [[Fantastic Fest]] in Austin<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fantasticfest.com/films/belladonna-of-sadness |title=''Belladonna of Sadness'' |publisher=[[Fantastic Fest]] |accessdate=June 9, 2016| archivedate=March 22, 2016 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160322005310/http://fantasticfest.com/films/belladonna-of-sadness | url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Exclusive: Inside Japan\u2019s Lost Erotic \u201970s Anime \u2018Belladonna of Sadness\u2019  |url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2015/09/28/exclusive-inside-japan-s-lost-erotic-70s-anime-belladonna-of-sadness.html |author=Jen Yamato |date=2015-09-27 |accessdate=2016-06-09 |publisher=TheDailyBeast.com|archivedate= January 25, 2016| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20160125070156/http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2015/09/28/exclusive-inside-japan-s-lost-erotic-70s-anime-belladonna-of-sadness.html | url-status =live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2015/09/23/fantastic-fest-2015-16-must-see-movies |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |title=16 must-see movies at Fantastic Fest 2015 |first=Clark|last= Collis |accessdate=June 9, 2016| archivedate=November 1, 2015 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151101091837/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/09/23/fantastic-fest-2015-16-must-see-movies | url-status=live}}</ref> before a theatrical run beginning May 6, 2016 in New York City and San Francisco.<ref>{{cite web|title=Review: \u2018Belladonna of Sadness,\u2019 a Bewitching Masterpiece |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/05/06/movies/belladonna-of-sadness-review-japanese-animation.html |first=Glenn |last=Kenny |date=May 5, 2016 |accessdate=June 9, 2016 |archivedate=June 13, 2016 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6iDqckmEw?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/05/06/movies/belladonna-of-sadness-review-japanese-animation.html?_r=0 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/05/06/elijah-wood-belladonna-sadness |work=Entertainment Weekly |title=See why Elijah Wood's mind was blown by animated film Belladonna of Sadness\u2014Exclusive clip |first=Clark|last= Collis |date=May 6, 2016 |accessdate=June 9, 2016| archivedate= May 16, 2016| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160516085850/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/05/06/elijah-wood-belladonna-sadness| url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2016/02/watch-long-lost-belladonna-of-sadness-gets-a-psychedelic-nsfw-trailer-67920/ |publisher=Indiewire.com |title=Watch: Long-Lost \u2018Belladonna of Sadness\u2019 Gets a Psychedelic NSFW Trailer |accessdate=June 9, 2016|archivedate=June 13, 2016 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613003520/http://www.indiewire.com/2016/02/watch-long-lost-belladonna-of-sadness-gets-a-psychedelic-nsfw-trailer-67920/ | url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBecause of the film's obscurity, various sources list its running time as anywhere from 86 to 93 minutes. [[Cinelicious Pics]] clarified in May 2016 that its 86-minute restoration represented the correct running time, saying that this length had been {{quote|cut down by approximately eight minutes for an unsuccessful re-release in Japan in 1979 (with the addition of the brief ending shot of Eugene Delacroix's painting ''[[Liberty Leading the People]]'', which wasn't in the original version\u2014Cinelicious left it in this restored version). Cinelicious restored the censored footage from the sole surviving 35mm release print of the full-length version at the Cinematek in Belgium, which very graciously agreed to do a 4K scan of the missing sections from their print.<ref name=FJI>Cinelicious Pics spokesperson quoted in {{cite news| url=http://www.filmjournal.com/reviews/film-review-belladonna-sadness|title=Film Review: Belladonna of Sadness||first= Frank|last= Lovece |date=May 5, 2016|accessdate= June 12, 2016| work=[[Film Journal International]] | archivedate=June 13, 2016| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613001212/http://www.filmjournal.com/reviews/film-review-belladonna-sadness | url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of animated feature-length films]]\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{Reflist|group=n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0071203}}\n* {{Amg movie|155590}}\n* {{ann|film|1723}}\n* {{YouTube|2WkcLMapo_Y|Cinelicious trailer}}\n* {{YouTube|uIs1CT__ZBM|Original Japanese trailer}}\n\n{{Osamu Tezuka}}\n\n[[Category:1973 anime films]]\n[[Category:Adult animated films]]\n[[Category:Animated feature films]]\n[[Category:Films about sexuality]]\n[[Category:Films based on non-fiction books]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Eiichi Yamamoto]]\n[[Category:Films about Joan of Arc]]\n[[Category:Osamu Tezuka anime]]\n[[Category:Mushi Production]]\n[[Category:Japanese films]]\n[[Category:Films about witchcraft]]\n", "name_user": "Vallier59", "label": "safe", "comment": "improved Jules Michelet", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belladonna_of_Sadness"}
{"title_page": "Cherukupalle mandal", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Cherukupalli mandal\n| official_name           = Cherukupalle H/O Arumbaka mandal\n| native_name             = \n| native_name_lang        = te\n| settlement_type         = [[Mandal]]\n| image_skyline           = File:Cherukupalle mandal in Guntur district.jpg\n| image_alt               =\n| image_caption           = Mandal map of Guntur district showing Cherukupalle mandal (in yellow)\n| nickname                =\n| pushpin_map             = India Andhra Pradesh#India\n| pushpin_label_position  = Cherukupalli\n| pushpin_map_alt         =\n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Andhra Pradesh, India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|16.04825|N|80.67561|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = [[India]]\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_type3       = [[List of mandals in Andhra Pradesh|Mandal]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Andhra Pradesh]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Guntur district|Guntur]]\n| subdivision_name3       = Cherukupalli\n| established_title       = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date        = 25 May 1985\n| founder                 =\n| named_for               =\n| parts_type              =\n| parts                   =\n| government_type         =\n| governing_body          =\n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_footnotes          = <ref name=census>{{cite web|title=District Census Handbook \u2013 Guntur|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/dchb/2817_PART_B_DCHB_GUNTUR.pdf|website=Census of India|accessdate=20 February 2016|pages=14}}</ref>\n| area_total_km2          = 98.97\n| area_rank               =\n| elevation_footnotes     = <ref>{{cite web|title=Elevation for Pedakurapadu|url=http://veloroutes.org/elevation/?location=Cherukupalli&units=m|publisher=Veloroutes|accessdate=1 August 2014}}</ref>\n| elevation_m             = 9\n| population_total        = 60385\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_footnotes    = <ref name=\"census\" />\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_rank         =\n| population_demonym      =\n| demographics_type1      = Languages\n| demographics1_title1    = Official\n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code             = 522 309\n| area_code               = 08648\n| area_code_type          = [[Telephone numbers in India|Telephone code]]\n| registration_plate      =\n| website                 =\n| footnotes               =\n| demographics1_info1     = [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n}}\n\n[[File:Cherukupalli Centre.jpg|thumb|right|Cherukupalli Centre]]\n'''Cherukupalli mandal''' (officially:'''Cherukupalle H/O Arumbaka mandal''') is one of the fifty seven mandals in [[Guntur district]] of the [[Indian state]] of [[Andhra Pradesh]]. It is under the administration of [[Tenali revenue division]] of the district. The village of Cherukupalle is the administrative seat of the mandal.<ref name=\"census\" />\n\n== History ==\n\nThis area may be under Kingdom of Prataliputra (5th century BC)}, identified with Bhattiprolu (10&nbsp;km away), the earliest known kingdom in Guntur District. Inscriptional evidence shows that king Kubera was ruling over Bhattiprolu around 230 BC followed by the Sala Kings. This area used to be under Nizampatnam Circar during Golconda Sultanate and Nizam times. Nizampatnam circar was transferred to French and then on to British for the help rendered during the Carnatic wars. \n\nThe village of Arepalli was granted as Inam in the year 1688 (Salivahana era 1610) by Rajas of Komaravole, residents of Nizampatnam to certain Brahmins for religious purposes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.casemine.com/judgement/in/56b4961c607dba348f016b9b|title=V. Seethaya And Others v. P. Subramanya Somayajulu And Another {{!}} Privy Council {{!}} Judgment {{!}} Law {{!}} CaseMine|website=www.casemine.com|access-date=2019-06-16}}</ref> \"A manual of Krishna District: Madras Presidency\" compiled in the year 1881\u201382 also mentions the villages Ponnapalli and Arepalli as inam villages and the present area under Repalli Taluka.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=H74RAAAAYAAJ|title=A Manual of the Kistna District, in the Presidency of Madras: Compiled for the Government of Madras|date=1883-01-01|publisher=Lawrence Asylum Press|language=en}}</ref> The Cherukupalli Sub-District (Sub-Registrar) was formed in 1911 by removing some villages from Repalle, Bapatla and Guntur Taluks<ref>{{Cite book|title=Fort St.George Gazette 1910|last=|first=|publisher=Govt of Madras Presidency|year=|isbn=|location=Kerala state archives|pages=1833}}</ref>. The present sub-registrar office was constructed between 1926 and 1929<ref>{{Cite book|title=Fort St George Gazette|last=|first=|publisher=Madras Presidency|year=1926|url=http://statelibrary.kerala.gov.in/fort_gazette/index.php|location=Kerala state archives|pages=1058\u201360}}</ref> This area also finds mention in civil dispute case regarding Chennakesawara Swamy temple near cherukupalli in 1926 All India reporter<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.286052|title=All India Reporter|date=1926-01-01|publisher=D.V. Chitaley|language=en}}</ref>\n\nDuring freedom struggle, Nehru Granthalayam (library) was established in Gudavalli village as part of library movement to educate the people.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/historyoffreedom020146mbp/historyoffreedom020146mbp_djvu.txt|title=Full text of \"History Of Freedom Movement In Guntoor District121-147\"|website=archive.org|access-date=2016-09-07|publisher=PRASANNA PUBLICATIONS}}</ref> Mahatma Gandhi visited the mandal in 23 December 1933 as part of harijan upliftment tour. He laid foundation for Vinayashram building in Kavuru village, opened temple for harijans and gave a short speech.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://wikilivres.ca/wiki/Chronology_of_Mahatma_Gandhi's_life/India_1933|title=Chronology of Mahatma Gandhi's life/India 1933 \u2013 Wikilivres|website=wikilivres.ca|access-date=2016-09-07}}</ref> A tree planted by Gandhiji in 1933 is still alive in this ashramam. Gandhiji again visited Vinayashram on 23 January 1937 during his tour of cyclone effected areas of coastal Andhra. Another ashramam (Maitreya Ashramam) to his memory was established in Gudavalli village and functions till date.\n\nSri Gollapudi Sita Rama Shastri (Swami Sitaram), a gandhian was instrumental in establishing Vinaya Ashram (now Krishi Vignana Kendra) in Kavuru Village. During Quit India movement, he led a group of people who set fire to Sub Registrar office at Cherukupalli.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tera-3.ul.cs.cmu.edu/NASD/4a7f1db4-5792-415c-be79-266f41eef20a/upgrade-archive-06-14-2007/data/upload-allbooks/disk%203/Jan%20N/ENGLISH/Mahatma_Gandhis_Leadership_And_Quit_India_Movement_In_Coastal_Andhra/HTML/00000105.htm|title=00000105.htm|publisher=|access-date=2 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160807144807/http://tera-3.ul.cs.cmu.edu/NASD/4a7f1db4-5792-415c-be79-266f41eef20a/upgrade-archive-06-14-2007/data/upload-allbooks/disk%203/Jan%20N/ENGLISH/Mahatma_Gandhis_Leadership_And_Quit_India_Movement_In_Coastal_Andhra/HTML/00000105.htm|archive-date=7 August 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> He also undertook fast unto death for creation of separate Andhra state from his ashram at Kavuru, but gave up his 35-day fast under the advice from Vinobha Bhave.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ap.gov.in/about-ap/history/struggle-for-andhra-state/|title=Struggle for Andhra State \u2013 History of AP \u2013 Official AP State Government Portal {{!}} AP State Portal|website=www.ap.gov.in|access-date=2016-08-02}}</ref> On 29 May 1975 a group of naxalites attacked Cherukupalli police station and decamped with police weapons \u2013 a first in the state's history.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Former-Naxal-leaders-passes-away/articleshow/8702006.cms|title=Former Naxal leaders passes away \u2013 Times of India|access-date=2016-08-02}}</ref> This gave jolt to the police, who until then considered naxalites were confined only to the forests.\n\n== Geography ==\nThe mandal is bounded by [[Nagaram, Guntur district|Nagaram]] mandal towards south, [[Amruthalur]] mandal towards north, [[Pittalavanipalem]] mandal towards south, [[Bhattiprolu mandal]] towards east.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mandals in Guntur district|url=http://www.aponline.gov.in/quick%20links/apfactfile/info%20on%20districts/guntur.html|publisher=aponline.gov.in|accessdate=28 July 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150428070826/http://www.aponline.gov.in/quick%20links/apfactfile/info%20on%20districts/guntur.html|archivedate=28 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| title=Adminsistrative divisions of Guntur district| url=http://guntur.nic.in/statistics/ataglance.pdf| publisher=guntur.nic.in| accessdate=26 May 2014| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140626041854/http://guntur.nic.in/statistics/ataglance.pdf| archive-date=26 June 2014| url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n'''Climate'''\n\nThe mandal receives rainfall from South-West monsoon in the months of June-Sept. The average annual rainfall is 875&nbsp;mm.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web |url=http://guntur.nic.in/statistics/ataglance.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=2 August 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140626041854/http://guntur.nic.in/statistics/ataglance.pdf |archive-date=26 June 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Average rainfall (mm)\n! colspan=\"3\" |Actual Rainfall (mm)\n|-\n|2010\n|2011\n|2012\n|-\n|875.0\n|1389.6\n|457.6\n|973.4\n|}\nThe average monthly rainfall in mandal is as follows<ref name=\":1\" />\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Month\n!January\n!February\n!March\n!April\n!May\n!June\n!July\n!August\n!September\n!October\n!November\n!December\n|-\n|Average rainfall (mm)\n|13.1\n|8.4\n|3.7\n|6.4\n|62.7\n|85.7\n|127.9\n|138.3\n|157.0\n|143.0\n|102.2\n|26.6\n|}\n\n== Demographics ==\n{{As of|2011}} [[Census of India|census]], the mandal had a population of 60,385. The total population constitute, 29,852 males and 30,533 females \u2014a sex ratio of 1024 females per 1000 males. 5,371 children are in the age group of 0\u20136 years, of which 2,748 are boys and 2,623\nare girls. The average literacy rate stands at 66.88% with 36,795 literates.<ref name=census />{{rp|480}}<ref name=\"stats\">{{cite web|title=HAND BOOK OF STATISTICS 2013 GUNTUR DISTRICT|url=http://desap.cgg.gov.in/jsp/social/Guntur%20District%20DHB%20-%202013.pdf|accessdate=9 September 2016|pages=xi,3}}</ref>\n\n== Government and politics ==\n\n=== Administration ===\n\nThe mandal consist 10 revenue villages, 16 panchayats and 49 hamlets.<ref name=census />{{rp|480}}<ref name=stats />{{rp|7}}\n\nThe area used to be part of Tenali Taluka and later came under newly formed Repalle Taluka from 1909. Again in 1981\u201382 this mandal came under Pallapatla taluka after bifurcation of Repalle Taluka. Cherukupalli mandal came into existence from 25-5-1985 as per govt. decision to form new administrative units called mandals.<ref name=\":1\" />\nThe settlements in the mandal are listed below:\n\n{{Columns-list|colwidth=30em|style=width:450px;|\n# Arepalli\n# Arumbaka\u2020\n# Balusupalem\n# [[Gudavalli, Guntur district|Gudavalli]]\n# Kaavuru\n# [[Kanagala]]\n# [[Nadimpalli]]\n# [[Ponnapalli]]\n# Rajavolu\n# Rambhotlapalem\n}}\n''\u2020\u2212Mandal headquarters''\n\n=== Politics ===\nCherukupalli mandal falls under [[Bapatla (SC) (Lok Sabha constituency)|Baptla Parliamentary constituency]], represented by [[Nandhigama Suresh]] of [[YSRCP]]. It in turn is a part of [[Repalle (Assembly constituency)|Repalle assembly constituency]], represented by [[Anagani Satya Prasad]] from tdp. The mandal administration is under the Cherukupalli Mandal Parishad, a local self-government, established under AP Panchayati Raj act, 1994. The present Mandal Parishad president is M.Parvathi of TDP.<ref name=mpp>{{cite web|title=4th Ordinary Elections to MPTC / ZPTC, 2014|url=http://www.apsec.gov.in/ELECTIONRESULTS/RESULTS%202014/MPP%20ELECTED%20MEMBERS,%202014(ANDHRA).pdf|website=Andhra Pradesh State Election Commission|accessdate=12 September 2016}}</ref> In the local government elections held in 2014, Pitlu Srinivasa Reddy won from Cherukupalli ZPTC (ZIlla Parishad Territorial Constituency).<ref name=zpm>{{cite web|title=4th Ordinary Elections to MPTC / ZPTC, 2014|url=http://www.apsec.gov.in/ELECTIONRESULTS/RESULTS%202014/Andhra%20Elected%20ZPTCs%20List,%202014.pdf|website=Andhra Pradesh State Election Commission|accessdate=12 September 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe list of Mandal Parishad members elected in 2014 elections are as below.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.apsec.gov.in/RLBS_RESULTS.html|title=STATE ELECTION COMMISSION, ANDHRA PRADESH|website=www.apsec.gov.in|access-date=2016-08-04}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!S.No.\n!Constituency\n!Reservation\n!MPTC Member\n!Political Party\n|-\n|1\n|Arepalli\n|UR(W)\n|Mathi Vijaya Lakshmi\n|YSRCP\n|-\n|2\n|Arumbaka\n|SC\n|Vemu Mohanbabu\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|3\n|Balusulapalem\n|UR\n|Yarramsetty Venkata Srinivasa Rao\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|4\n|Cherukupalli-1\n|SC(W)\n|Naidu Padma\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|5\n|Cherukupalli-2\n|UR(W)\n|Mokhamatam Parvathi\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|6\n|Gudavalli\n|UR\n|Gaddipati Venkateswara Rao\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|7\n|Gullapalli-1\n|ST(W)\n|Savanam Padma\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|8\n|Gullapalli-2\n|BC\n|Yaragalla Amareswari\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|9\n|Kanagala-1\n|UR\n|Abdul Ahad\n|YSRCP\n|-\n|10\n|Kanagala-2\n|UR(W)\n|Dhoopam Samrajyam\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|11\n|Kavuru\n|BC(W)\n|Yalavarthi Tirumala Rani\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|12\n|Nadimpalli\n|UR(W)\n|Uppala Swetha\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|13\n|Ponnapalli\n|BC(W)\n|Puli Vijaya Lakshmi\n|YSRCP\n|-\n|14\n|Rajavolu\n|UR(W)\n|Dontuboina Samrajyam\n|YSRCP\n|-\n|15\n|Rambhotlapalem\n|BC\n|Janni Sambasiva Rao\n|YSRCP\n|-\n|16\n|Thurpupalem\n|UR\n|Pushadapu Venkata Srinivasa Rao\n|YSRCP\n|-\n|17\n|Tummalapalem\n|UR\n|Akkala Venkata Krishna Reddy\n|YSRCP\n|}\n\nThe below table lists all the presidents elected for mandal parishad.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Election Years\n!Mandal Parishad President\n!Political Party\n|-\n|2001\n|Pushadapu Siva Ganga Parvathy<ref>{{cite web|title=4th Ordinary Elections to MPTC / ZPTC, 2014|url=http://www.apsec.gov.in/ELECTIONRESULTS/MP%20Presidents%202001.pdf|website=Andhra Pradesh State Election Commission|accessdate=12 September 2016}}</ref>\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|2006\n|Chennu Koteswara Rao<ref>{{cite web|title=4th Ordinary Elections to MPTC / ZPTC, 2014|url=http://www.apsec.gov.in/ELECTIONRESULTS/MP%20Presidents%202006.pdf|website=Andhra Pradesh State Election Commission|accessdate=12 September 2016}}</ref>\n|INC\n|-\n|2014\n|M.Parvathi<ref name=\"mpp\" />\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|}\n\n== Economy ==\nMother Teressa Swachanda Seva Samstha at Cherukupalle and Sharon International Ministries at Kurrapalem, Gullapalli village are the only two NGOs in the mandal are cleared to receive foreign donations under Foreign Contribution Regulation Act (FCRA).<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://fcraonline.nic.in/home/index.aspx#|title=Fcra OnLine Services|last=|first=|date=|website=fcraonline.nic.in|publisher=|access-date=2016-09-07}}</ref>\n\nThree Primary Agricultural Credit Co-operative Societies (PACS) are active in the mandal at Kavuru, Gudavalli, Nadimpalli.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://gunturdccb.com/affiliated-packs/ | title=Affiliated PACS}}</ref> Milk Producers MACS (Nadimpalli, Cherukupalli, Vuchavaripalem, Pooshadapuvaripalem, Podilivaripalem, Ponnapalli, Balusulapalem, Gullapalli, Arepalli, Rajavolu, Kanagala, Gudavalli, Kaminenivaripalem, Yeminenivaripalem); Mutually Aided Coop.Thrift Village Societies (MACTVS) in all the villages the mandal; Cherukupalli Santhi Sree Mandal Women MATC Federation Ltd; Pagadavaripalem Mahila TMACPS; Pittukotireddypalem Mahila TMACPS are some of the other.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cooperation.ap.gov.in/mas.html|title=Coop--Movement|website=www.cooperation.ap.gov.in|access-date=2016-09-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160916181551/http://www.cooperation.ap.gov.in/mas.html|archive-date=16 September 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Education ==\n66 Anganwadi Centres (AWC) operate in the mandal providing nutrition and pre-school education. The mandal has some of the oldest and famous govt schools like Muniwamy Nadiu ZP school, Gudavalli established in 1944, Cherukupalli ZPH school, Kavuru ZPH school. A Govt BC Boys welfare hostel is located at Gullapalli. Apart from this 1 SC boys hostel and 1 SC girls hostel also operate in the mandal. Kavuru govt junior college, Nagarjuna Junior College at Cherukupalle and Cherukupalle Junior College are the notable junior colleges in the mandal.<ref>{{cite web|title=LIST OF COLLEGES IN GUNTUR DISTRICT|url=http://bieap.gov.in/Pdf/guntur.pdf|website=Board of Intermediate Education|accessdate=9 September 2016}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Mandal headquarters in Guntur district}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cherukupalli Mandal}}\n[[Category:Mandal headquarters in Guntur district]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Cherukupalli mandal\n| official_name           = Cherukupalle H/O Arumbaka mandal\n| native_name             = \n| native_name_lang        = te\n| settlement_type         = [[Mandal]]\n| image_skyline           = File:Cherukupalle mandal in Guntur district.jpg\n| image_alt               =\n| image_caption           = Mandal map of Guntur district showing Cherukupalle mandal (in yellow)\n| nickname                =\n| pushpin_map             = India Andhra Pradesh#India\n| pushpin_label_position  = Cherukupalli\n| pushpin_map_alt         =\n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Andhra Pradesh, India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|16.04825|N|80.67561|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = [[India]]\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_type3       = [[List of mandals in Andhra Pradesh|Mandal]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Andhra Pradesh]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Guntur district|Guntur]]\n| subdivision_name3       = Cherukupalli\n| established_title       = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date        = 25 May 1985\n| founder                 =\n| named_for               =\n| parts_type              =\n| parts                   =\n| government_type         =\n| governing_body          =\n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_footnotes          = <ref name=census>{{cite web|title=District Census Handbook \u2013 Guntur|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/dchb/2817_PART_B_DCHB_GUNTUR.pdf|website=Census of India|accessdate=20 February 2016|pages=14}}</ref>\n| area_total_km2          = 98.97\n| area_rank               =\n| elevation_footnotes     = <ref>{{cite web|title=Elevation for Pedakurapadu|url=http://veloroutes.org/elevation/?location=Cherukupalli&units=m|publisher=Veloroutes|accessdate=1 August 2014}}</ref>\n| elevation_m             = 9\n| population_total        = 60385\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_footnotes    = <ref name=\"census\" />\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_rank         =\n| population_demonym      =\n| demographics_type1      = Languages\n| demographics1_title1    = Official\n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code             = 522 309\n| area_code               = 08648\n| area_code_type          = [[Telephone numbers in India|Telephone code]]\n| registration_plate      =\n| website                 =\n| footnotes               =\n| demographics1_info1     = [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n}}\n\n[[File:Cherukupalli Centre.jpg|thumb|right|Cherukupalli Centre]]\n'''Cherukupalli mandal''' (officially:'''Cherukupalle H/O Arumbaka mandal''') is one of the fifty seven mandals in [[Guntur district]] of the [[Indian state]] of [[Andhra Pradesh]]. It is under the administration of [[Tenali revenue division]] of the district. The village of Cherukupalle is the administrative seat of the mandal.<ref name=\"census\" />\n\n== History ==\n\nThis area may be under Kingdom of Prataliputra (5th century BC)}, identified with Bhattiprolu (10kms away), the earliest known kingdom in Guntur District. Inscriptional evidence shows that king Kubera was ruling over Bhattiprolu around 230 BC followed by the Sala Kings. This area used to be under Nizampatnam Circar during Golconda Sultanate and Nizam times. Nizampatnam circar was transferred to French and then on to British for the help rendered during the Carnatic wars. \n\nThe village of Arepalli was granted as Inam in the year 1688 (Salivahana era 1610) by Rajas of Komaravole, residents of Nizampatnam to certain Brahmins for religious purposes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.casemine.com/judgement/in/56b4961c607dba348f016b9b|title=V. Seethaya And Others v. P. Subramanya Somayajulu And Another {{!}} Privy Council {{!}} Judgment {{!}} Law {{!}} CaseMine|website=www.casemine.com|access-date=2019-06-16}}</ref> \"A manual of Krishna District: Madras Presidency\" compiled in the year 1881\u201382 also mentions the villages Ponnapalli and Arepalli as inam villages and the present area under Repalli Taluka.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=H74RAAAAYAAJ|title=A Manual of the Kistna District, in the Presidency of Madras: Compiled for the Government of Madras|date=1883-01-01|publisher=Lawrence Asylum Press|language=en}}</ref> The Cherukupalli Sub-District (Sub-Registar) was formed in 1911 by removing some villages from Repalle, Bapatla and Guntur Taluks<ref>{{Cite book|title=Fort St.George Gazette 1910|last=|first=|publisher=Govt of Madras Presidency|year=|isbn=|location=Kerala state archives|pages=1833}}</ref>. The present sub-registar office was constructed between 1926 and 1929<ref>{{Cite book|title=Fort St George Gazette|last=|first=|publisher=Madras Presidency|year=1926|url=http://statelibrary.kerala.gov.in/fort_gazette/index.php|location=Kerala state archives|pages=1058\u201360}}</ref> This area also finds mention in civil dispute case regarding Chennakesawara Swamy temple near cherukupalli in 1926 All India reporter<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.286052|title=All India Reporter|date=1926-01-01|publisher=D.V. Chitaley|language=en}}</ref>\n\nDuring freedom struggle, Nehru Granthalayam (library) was established in Gudavalli village as part of library movement to educate the people.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/historyoffreedom020146mbp/historyoffreedom020146mbp_djvu.txt|title=Full text of \"History Of Freedom Movement In Guntoor District121-147\"|website=archive.org|access-date=2016-09-07|publisher=PRASANNA PUBLICATIONS}}</ref> Mahatma Gandhi visited the mandal in 23 December 1933 as part of harijan upliftment tour. He laid foundation for Vinayashram building in Kavuru village, opened temple for harijans and gave a short speech.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://wikilivres.ca/wiki/Chronology_of_Mahatma_Gandhi's_life/India_1933|title=Chronology of Mahatma Gandhi's life/India 1933 \u2013 Wikilivres|website=wikilivres.ca|access-date=2016-09-07}}</ref> A tree planted by Gandhiji in 1933 is still alive in this ashramam. Gandhiji again visited Vinayashram on 23 January 1937 during his tour of cyclone effected areas of coastal Andhra. Another ashramam (Maitreya Ashramam) to his memory was established in Gudavalli village and functions till date.\n\nSri Gollapudi Sita Rama Shastri (Swami Sitaram), a gandhian was instrumental in establishing Vinaya Ashram (now Krishi Vignana Kendra) in Kavuru Village. During Quit India movement, he led a group of people who set fire to Sub Registrar office at Cherukupalli.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tera-3.ul.cs.cmu.edu/NASD/4a7f1db4-5792-415c-be79-266f41eef20a/upgrade-archive-06-14-2007/data/upload-allbooks/disk%203/Jan%20N/ENGLISH/Mahatma_Gandhis_Leadership_And_Quit_India_Movement_In_Coastal_Andhra/HTML/00000105.htm|title=00000105.htm|publisher=|access-date=2 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160807144807/http://tera-3.ul.cs.cmu.edu/NASD/4a7f1db4-5792-415c-be79-266f41eef20a/upgrade-archive-06-14-2007/data/upload-allbooks/disk%203/Jan%20N/ENGLISH/Mahatma_Gandhis_Leadership_And_Quit_India_Movement_In_Coastal_Andhra/HTML/00000105.htm|archive-date=7 August 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> He also undertook fast unto death for creation of separate Andhra state from his ashram at Kavuru, but gave up his 35-day fast under the advice from Vinobha Bhave.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ap.gov.in/about-ap/history/struggle-for-andhra-state/|title=Struggle for Andhra State \u2013 History of AP \u2013 Official AP State Government Portal {{!}} AP State Portal|website=www.ap.gov.in|access-date=2016-08-02}}</ref> On 29 May 1975 a group of naxalites attacked Cherukupalli police station and decamped with police weapons \u2013 a first in the state's history.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Former-Naxal-leaders-passes-away/articleshow/8702006.cms|title=Former Naxal leaders passes away \u2013 Times of India|access-date=2016-08-02}}</ref> This gave jolt to the police, who until then considered naxalites were confined only to the forests.\n\n== Geography ==\nThe mandal is bounded by [[Nagaram, Guntur district|Nagaram]] mandal towards south, [[Amruthalur]] mandal towards north, [[Pittalavanipalem]] mandal towards south, [[Bhattiprolu mandal]] towards east.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mandals in Guntur district|url=http://www.aponline.gov.in/quick%20links/apfactfile/info%20on%20districts/guntur.html|publisher=aponline.gov.in|accessdate=28 July 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150428070826/http://www.aponline.gov.in/quick%20links/apfactfile/info%20on%20districts/guntur.html|archivedate=28 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| title=Adminsistrative divisions of Guntur district| url=http://guntur.nic.in/statistics/ataglance.pdf| publisher=guntur.nic.in| accessdate=26 May 2014| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140626041854/http://guntur.nic.in/statistics/ataglance.pdf| archive-date=26 June 2014| url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n'''Climate'''\n\nThe mandal receives rainfall from South-West monsoon in the months of June-Sept. The average annual rainfall is 875&nbsp;mm.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web |url=http://guntur.nic.in/statistics/ataglance.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=2 August 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140626041854/http://guntur.nic.in/statistics/ataglance.pdf |archive-date=26 June 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Average rainfall (mm)\n! colspan=\"3\" |Actual Rainfall (mm)\n|-\n|2010\n|2011\n|2012\n|-\n|875.0\n|1389.6\n|457.6\n|973.4\n|}\nThe average monthly rainfall in mandal is as follows<ref name=\":1\" />\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Month\n!January\n!February\n!March\n!April\n!May\n!June\n!July\n!August\n!September\n!October\n!November\n!December\n|-\n|Average rainfall (mm)\n|13.1\n|8.4\n|3.7\n|6.4\n|62.7\n|85.7\n|127.9\n|138.3\n|157.0\n|143.0\n|102.2\n|26.6\n|}\n\n== Demographics ==\n{{As of|2011}} [[Census of India|census]], the mandal had a population of 60,385. The total population constitute, 29,852 males and 30,533 females \u2014a sex ratio of 1024 females per 1000 males. 5,371 children are in the age group of 0\u20136 years, of which 2,748 are boys and 2,623\nare girls. The average literacy rate stands at 66.88% with 36,795 literates.<ref name=census />{{rp|480}}<ref name=\"stats\">{{cite web|title=HAND BOOK OF STATISTICS 2013 GUNTUR DISTRICT|url=http://desap.cgg.gov.in/jsp/social/Guntur%20District%20DHB%20-%202013.pdf|accessdate=9 September 2016|pages=xi,3}}</ref>\n\n== Government and politics ==\n\n=== Administration ===\n\nThe mandal consist 10 revenue villages, 16 panchayats and 49 hamlets.<ref name=census />{{rp|480}}<ref name=stats />{{rp|7}}\n\nThe area used to be part of Tenali Taluka and later came under newly formed Repalle Taluka from 1909. Again in 1981\u201382 this mandal came under Pallapatla taluka after bifurcation of Repalle Taluka. Cherukupalli mandal came into existence from 25-5-1985 as per govt. decision to form new administrative units called mandals.<ref name=\":1\" />\nThe settlements in the mandal are listed below:\n\n{{Columns-list|colwidth=30em|style=width:450px;|\n# Arepalli\n# Arumbaka\u2020\n# Balusupalem\n# [[Gudavalli, Guntur district|Gudavalli]]\n# Kaavuru\n# [[Kanagala]]\n# [[Nadimpalli]]\n# [[Ponnapalli]]\n# Rajavolu\n# Rambhotlapalem\n}}\n''\u2020\u2212Mandal headquarters''\n\n=== Politics ===\nCherukupalli mandal falls under [[Bapatla (SC) (Lok Sabha constituency)|Baptla Parliamentary constituency]], represented by [[Nandhigama Suresh]] of [[YSRCP]]. It in turn is a part of [[Repalle (Assembly constituency)|Repalle assembly constituency]], represented by [[Anagani Satya Prasad]] from tdp. The mandal administration is under the Cherukupalli Mandal Parishad, a local self-government, established under AP Panchayati Raj act, 1994. The present Mandal Parishad president is M.Parvathi of TDP.<ref name=mpp>{{cite web|title=4th Ordinary Elections to MPTC / ZPTC, 2014|url=http://www.apsec.gov.in/ELECTIONRESULTS/RESULTS%202014/MPP%20ELECTED%20MEMBERS,%202014(ANDHRA).pdf|website=Andhra Pradesh State Election Commission|accessdate=12 September 2016}}</ref> In the local government elections held in 2014, Pitlu Srinivasa Reddy won from Cherukupalli ZPTC (ZIlla Parishad Territorial Constituency).<ref name=zpm>{{cite web|title=4th Ordinary Elections to MPTC / ZPTC, 2014|url=http://www.apsec.gov.in/ELECTIONRESULTS/RESULTS%202014/Andhra%20Elected%20ZPTCs%20List,%202014.pdf|website=Andhra Pradesh State Election Commission|accessdate=12 September 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe list of Mandal Parishad members elected in 2014 elections are as below.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.apsec.gov.in/RLBS_RESULTS.html|title=STATE ELECTION COMMISSION, ANDHRA PRADESH|website=www.apsec.gov.in|access-date=2016-08-04}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!S.No.\n!Constituency\n!Reservation\n!MPTC Member\n!Political Party\n|-\n|1\n|Arepalli\n|UR(W)\n|Mathi Vijaya Lakshmi\n|YSRCP\n|-\n|2\n|Arumbaka\n|SC\n|Vemu Mohanbabu\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|3\n|Balusulapalem\n|UR\n|Yarramsetty Venkata Srinivasa Rao\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|4\n|Cherukupalli-1\n|SC(W)\n|Naidu Padma\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|5\n|Cherukupalli-2\n|UR(W)\n|Mokhamatam Parvathi\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|6\n|Gudavalli\n|UR\n|Gaddipati Venkateswara Rao\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|7\n|Gullapalli-1\n|ST(W)\n|Savanam Padma\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|8\n|Gullapalli-2\n|BC\n|Yaragalla Amareswari\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|9\n|Kanagala-1\n|UR\n|Abdul Ahad\n|YSRCP\n|-\n|10\n|Kanagala-2\n|UR(W)\n|Dhoopam Samrajyam\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|11\n|Kavuru\n|BC(W)\n|Yalavarthi Tirumala Rani\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|12\n|Nadimpalli\n|UR(W)\n|Uppala Swetha\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|13\n|Ponnapalli\n|BC(W)\n|Puli Vijaya Lakshmi\n|YSRCP\n|-\n|14\n|Rajavolu\n|UR(W)\n|Dontuboina Samrajyam\n|YSRCP\n|-\n|15\n|Rambhotlapalem\n|BC\n|Janni Sambasiva Rao\n|YSRCP\n|-\n|16\n|Thurpupalem\n|UR\n|Pushadapu Venkata Srinivasa Rao\n|YSRCP\n|-\n|17\n|Tummalapalem\n|UR\n|Akkala Venkata Krishna Reddy\n|YSRCP\n|}\n\nThe below table lists all the presidents elected for mandal parishad.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Election Years\n!Mandal Parishad President\n!Political Party\n|-\n|2001\n|Pushadapu Siva Ganga Parvathy<ref>{{cite web|title=4th Ordinary Elections to MPTC / ZPTC, 2014|url=http://www.apsec.gov.in/ELECTIONRESULTS/MP%20Presidents%202001.pdf|website=Andhra Pradesh State Election Commission|accessdate=12 September 2016}}</ref>\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|-\n|2006\n|Chennu Koteswara Rao<ref>{{cite web|title=4th Ordinary Elections to MPTC / ZPTC, 2014|url=http://www.apsec.gov.in/ELECTIONRESULTS/MP%20Presidents%202006.pdf|website=Andhra Pradesh State Election Commission|accessdate=12 September 2016}}</ref>\n|INC\n|-\n|2014\n|M.Parvathi<ref name=\"mpp\" />\n|[[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|}\n\n== Economy ==\nMother Teressa Swachanda Seva Samstha at Cherukupalle and Sharon International Ministries at Kurrapalem, Gullapalli village are the only two NGOs in the mandal are cleared to receive foreign donations under Foreign Contribution Regulation Act (FCRA).<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://fcraonline.nic.in/home/index.aspx#|title=Fcra OnLine Services|last=|first=|date=|website=fcraonline.nic.in|publisher=|access-date=2016-09-07}}</ref>\n\nThree Primary Agricultural Credit Co-operative Societies (PACS) are active in the mandal at Kavuru, Gudavalli, Nadimpalli.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://gunturdccb.com/affiliated-packs/ | title=Affiliated PACS}}</ref> Milk Producers MACS (Nadimpalli, Cherukupalli, Vuchavaripalem, Pooshadapuvaripalem, Podilivaripalem, Ponnapalli, Balusulapalem, Gullapalli, Arepalli, Rajavolu, Kanagala, Gudavalli, Kaminenivaripalem, Yeminenivaripalem); Mutually Aided Coop.Thrift Village Societies (MACTVS) in all the villages the mandal; Cherukupalli Santhi Sree Mandal Women MATC Federation Ltd; Pagadavaripalem Mahila TMACPS; Pittukotireddypalem Mahila TMACPS are some of the other.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cooperation.ap.gov.in/mas.html|title=Coop--Movement|website=www.cooperation.ap.gov.in|access-date=2016-09-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160916181551/http://www.cooperation.ap.gov.in/mas.html|archive-date=16 September 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Education ==\n66 Anganwadi Centres (AWC) operate in the mandal providing nutrition and pre-school education. The mandal has some of the oldest and famous govt schools like Muniwamy Nadiu ZP school, Gudavalli established in 1944, Cherukupalli ZPH school, Kavuru ZPH school. A Govt BC Boys welfare hostel is located at Gullapalli. Apart from this 1 SC boys hostel and 1 SC girls hostel also operate in the mandal. Kavuru govt junior college, Nagarjuna Junior College at Cherukupalle and Cherukupalle Junior College are the notable junior colleges in the mandal.<ref>{{cite web|title=LIST OF COLLEGES IN GUNTUR DISTRICT|url=http://bieap.gov.in/Pdf/guntur.pdf|website=Board of Intermediate Education|accessdate=9 September 2016}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Mandal headquarters in Guntur district}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cherukupalli Mandal}}\n[[Category:Mandal headquarters in Guntur district]]\n", "name_user": "WereSpielChequers", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eHistory:Typo fixing, replaced: registar  \u2192 registrar , Registar \u2192 Registrar,typo(s) fixed: 10kms \u2192 10\u00a0km", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cherukupalle_mandal"}
